Build bookworm-gnome sdcard for roc-rk3328-cc:

Input files: ../uboot/out/idbloader.img
             ../uboot/out/uboot.img
             ../uboot/out/trust.img
             ../linux/out/boot.img
             ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-rootfs.img

cd ~/build-roc-rk3328-cc/bookworm-gnome
Plugin sdcard to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject sdcard from PC.

Plugin sdcard, ethernet cable and ASUS bluetooth usb dongle to SBC.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
free
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools chromium chromium-sandbox vlc vlc-plugin-video-output ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-x11 pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2

aplay -l
pavucontrol

Chromium -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

Do follows on PC, then ftp swan.mp4 to roc-rk3328-cc.
(
git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4][protocol=https]+bestaudio[ext=m4a][protocol=https]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4 --postprocessor-args "-vf scale=1024:640 -r 10 -c:v libx264 -b:v 2M -c:a copy"
)

mpv --hwdec=auto-copy swan.mp4
ffplay swan.mp4
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
